,Recommended,404550,20597753,"Posted: 17 January, 2016",all,Woke Santa,"I am going to start out by saying that this game has an amazing concept, good gameplay and fun game mechanics. And The graphics are pretty basic, but good for what they are. It still needs some streamlining, but  Overall, this game is definately worth buying, especially considering that it will be updated and improved from here.There are some issues i would like to go over to help the developer(s?) improve the game.First of all, very occasionally (i think it happened to me about twice in almost 4 hours of gameplay) jack will simply not appear. And while we are on the issue of bugs i found that after i used the tractor about half the time i wouldn't find all of the food in my inventory when going to trade with jack. Closing and then re-opening trade with jack seemed to fix this. I didn't check in my inventory before going to trade though.Second of all i understand that there are tools you can buy to collect natural resources (mining rock ect.) but even with the tractor i just couldn't find the time to do this with all the improving defences and whatnot to be done.Third of all, i had some issues with the hammer. I bought it because i made some mistakes in my defence plan but i found that it just took to long to destroy objects. Especially if you've started building with stronger materials. So rather than help improve my defences i just wasted a bunch of time and then gave up on trying. So i think that it definately needs to destroy things faster.Lastly, i think that the whole turret system could use some streamlining. Maybe it's just me but i found i had to fiddle around with them alot. Maybe you could do something to make the whole generator thing easier?As for ideas of things to put in the game, i think it would be cool to see something like a slime shooter that shoots a huge spray of slime that slows down any zombie it hits, and traps with a limited number of uses would be cool too. Like a pit 